<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0199">
<l>oṉṟumuta lākap pattūrntu varūu</l>
<l>mellā veṇṇuñ colluṅ kālai</l>
<l>yāṉiṭai variṉu māṉa millai</l>
<l>yaḵteṉ kiḷavi yāvayiṟ keṭumē</l>
<l>yuytal vēṇṭum paḵkāṉ meyyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When pronouncing all numbers beginning with</l>
<l>one, and ending with ten, there is no harm</l>
<l>in <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṉ,</foreign> too, is added in the middle ;</l>
<l>if that case the part <foreign xml:lang="ta">aktu</foreign> [of <foreign xml:lang="ta">paḵtu</foreign>] is dropped ;</l>
<l>the consonant <foreign xml:lang="ta">p</foreign> must be preserved.<note place="foot">I.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">iru + pattu + ai &gt; </foreign>either <foreign xml:lang="ta">irupāṉai</foreign> (by rule 200) or <foreign xml:lang="ta">irupaḵtaṉai</foreign> (by rule 199).</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
